    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>MONTCLAIR TRAIN CONNECTION</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Karen DeMasters</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Demolition begins on 19 homes and apartment buildings in Montclair, NJ, as part of construction of new train connection to Manhattan's Penn Station (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Demolition began last week on 19 homes and apartment buildings in Montclair, the first step in the construction of the long-debated Montclair Connection, a 1,200-foot section of track that will give residents of Montclair, Bloomfield and Glen Ridge a direct rail line to Penn Station in Manhattan. Debate had centered on the 33 families, who have now been relocated for the connection to be built. Construction of the link is expected to be finished sometime next year.</p>
        <p>Karen DeMasters</p>
      </block>
